Minimum 6 years of experience as DataAnalyst with at least 3+ Years experience in Data Migration initiatives.

Strong functional understanding of RDBMS DWH-BI conceptual knowledge

Skillset :
Strong analytical skills with the ability to interpret data and provide insights to the client.
Proficiency in MS Office (Excel, PowerPoint) and data visualization tools like Power BI or Tableau.
Excellent communication, stakeholder management, and problem-solving abilities.
Experience working with multiple store formats and client-specific merchandising strategies.
Responsibilities:
Planogram & Space Optimization for the Client:
Develop and implement planograms tailored to the client s store formats and merchandising strategies.
Ensure that planograms align with the client s business objectives and localized assortment requirements.
Leverage space planning tools (JDA/Blue Yonder, Relex, etc.) to enhance product visibility and sales.
Operations & Execution:
Ensure accurate execution of the client s space planning and merchandising strategies.
Maintain governance and control over store layout data to ensure consistency across locations.
Track and improve key performance metrics related to space utilization, planogram compliance, and operational efficiency.
Stakeholder Management & Client Coordination:
Act as the primary point of contact for the client s teams regarding space planning and execution.
Work closely with the client s store managers, marketing, and operations teams to implement and optimize merchandising initiatives.
Provide regular updates and insights to the client, addressing concerns and ensuring alignment with their business goals.
Qualifications We Seek in You!
Minimum Qualifications:
Bachelors degree in Retail Management, Operations, Architecture, Civil Engineering, or related fields.
Experience in space planning, planogram development, and retail store layout optimization for clients.
Hands-on experience with space planning tools like JDA/Blue Yonder, Relex, Nexgen, or Apollo Retail.
Preferred Qualifications/Skills:
Strong analytical skills with the ability to interpret data and provide insights to the client.
Proficiency in MS Office (Excel, PowerPoint) and data visualization tools like Power BI or Tableau.
Excellent communication, stakeholder management, and problem-solving abilities.
Experience working with multiple store formats and client-specific merchandising strategies.
